title: cut NaNs from PanStarrs images and converts Variance image to Sigma Image
content:
#! /usr/bin/env python3

import numpy as np
import argparse
import os

from astropy.io import fits

# program to be used for panstarrs data
# Load your FITS file
def main():

    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description="resizes image to cutout nan regions and removes nan pixels. It optionally converts the variance image to sigma and resizes it")
    parser.add_argument("ImageFile", help="Fits image file")
    
    parser.add_argument("-var","--variance", type=str, help="the variance image file")

    args = parser.parse_args()
    image_file = args.ImageFile
    variance_file = args.variance


    if not os.path.exists(image_file):
        print ('{} image filename does not exist!'.format(image_file))
        sys.exit(1)

    if variance_file:
        if not os.path.exists(variance_file):
            print ('{} image filename does not exist!'.format(variance_file))
            sys.exit(1)



    hdul = fits.open(image_file)

    # Access the CompImageHDU (assuming it's the first extension)

    # Extract the data
    data = hdul[0].data

    valid_rows = ~np.isnan(data).all(axis=1)
    valid_cols = ~np.isnan(data).all(axis=0)

    cleaned_data = data[valid_rows][:, valid_cols]

    masknan = np.isnan(cleaned_data)
    cleaned_data[masknan] = 30000

    hdul[0].data= cleaned_data 
    hdul.writeto(image_file.replace("fits", "new.fits"), overwrite=True)
    hdul.close()



    if variance_file:

        hdus = fits.open(variance_file)
        var_data = hdus[0].data

        var_data[np.isnan(var_data)] = 1e7
        sig_data = np.sqrt(var_data)

        cleaned_sigma = sig_data[valid_rows][:, valid_cols]
        

        hdu_new = fits.PrimaryHDU(cleaned_sigma, hdus[0].header)
        hdu_new.header["IMTYPE"] = "sigma"
        hdu_new.header["BUNIT"] = "It is unkknown"
        hdu_new.writeto(variance_file.replace("fits", "sigma.fits"), overwrite=True)

   		hdus.close()



    print("Done")




if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()

title: BuildGenerator
content:
--#region variables
BuildingBlock='minecraft:cobblestone'
--#endregion variables
--#region functions
function ScanInventory()
    local amount={}
    local index={}
    for i=1,16,1 do
        local item=turtle.getItemDetail(i)
        if item then
            if not  index[item.name] then
                index[item.name]={}
            end
            table.insert(index[item.name],i)
            amount[item.name]=( amount[item.name] and  amount[item.name]+item.count) or item.count
        end
    end
    Index=index
    Amount=amount
end

function HasItems(needed,fuel,cobble)
    local fuels={['minecraft:lava_bucket']=2,['minecraft:coal']=1,['minecraft:charcoal']=1}
    for key, value in pairs(needed) do
        if not Amount[key] or Amount[key]<value then
            printError('Missing '..key..' have '..(Amount[key] or 0)..', '..value..' needed')
            return false
        end
    end
    if fuel then
        local fuellevel=turtle.getFuelLevel()
        if fuellevel < fuel then
            for key, value in pairs(fuels) do
                if Amount[key] and Amount[key]>=value then
                    SelectItem(key,value)
                    turtle.refuel(1)
                    fuellevel=turtle.getFuelLevel()
                    if fuellevel>fuel then
                        break
                    end
                end
            end
        end
        if fuellevel<fuel then
            printError('Missing fuel have '..fuellevel..', '..fuel..' needed')
            return false
        end
    end
    return true
end

function SelectItem(item,index)
    if Index[item] then
        turtle.select(Index[item][index or 1])
    else
        print(index..' not found for placing')
    end
end

function BuildBlueprint(blueprint)
    local actions={['F']=turtle.forward,['D']=turtle.down,['U']=turtle.up,
                   ['L']=turtle.turnLeft,['R']=turtle.turnRight,['B']=turtle.back,
                   ['d']=turtle.dig,['dD']=turtle.digDown,['dU']=turtle.digUp,
                   ['p']=turtle.place,['pD']=turtle.placeDown,['pU']=turtle.placeUp,
                   ['dr']=turtle.drop,['drD']=turtle.dropDown,['drU']=turtle.dropUp}
    for index, value in pairs(blueprint) do
        if actions[value]==nil then
            SelectItem(value)
        else
            actions[value]()
        end
    end
end



function tabCompletionFunction( curText)
	-- Check that the parameters entered so far are valid:
	local curParam = CurParam
	-- Check for suitable words for the current parameter:
	local results = {}
	for _, word  in pairs(curParam) do
		if word:sub(1, #curText) == curText then
			results[#results + 1] = word:sub(#curText + 1)
		end
	end
	return results
end

function OptionsRead(options) 
    local validate={}
    for index, value in ipairs(options) do
        validate[value]=true
    end
    CurParam=options
    local selection=nil
    repeat
        selection=read(nil,options,tabCompletionFunction)
        if not validate[selection] then
            printError('Option not valid')
        end
    until validate[selection] 
    return selection
end


function BasicGenerator()
    local needed={['minecraft:water_bucket']=1,['minecraft:lava_bucket']=1}
    local fuelneeded=2
    if HasItems(needed,fuelneeded) then
        local blueprint={'R','dD','D','d','dD','minecraft:water_bucket','p','L',
                         'L','d','F','d','minecraft:lava_bucket','p','U','L','L'}
        BuildBlueprint(blueprint)
        return true
    end
    return false
end

function DoubleFountain()
    local needed={['minecraft:water_bucket']=1,['minecraft:lava_bucket']=1,[BuildingBlock]=14}
    local fuelneeded=11
    if HasItems(needed,fuelneeded) then
        local blueprint={'R','F','dD','minecraft:cobblestone','p','L','p','B','R','p',
                        'R','p','R','F','F','p','L','p','B','p','R','p','R','p','U','p',
                        'L','p','B','B','R','p','R','p','U','pD','B','minecraft:water_bucket',
                        'p','L','L','minecraft:lava_bucket','p','D','L','L','d','R'}
        BuildBlueprint(blueprint)
        return true
    end
    return false
end

function BasaltGenerator()
    local needed={['minecraft:soul_soil']=2,['minecraft:blue_ice']=2,['minecraft:lava_bucket']=1,[BuildingBlock]=7}
    local fuelneeded=5
    if HasItems(needed,fuelneeded) then
        local blueprint={'L','dD','minecraft:soul_soil','p','pD','R','R','minecraft:blue_ice',
                        'p','L','F','minecraft:cobblestone','p','R','p','U','p','L','p','L',
                        'F','p','pD','R','p','B','L','minecraft:blue_ice','p','B','R',
                        'minecraft:lava_bucket','p','L'}
        BuildBlueprint(blueprint)
        return true
    end
    return false
end
--#endregion functions

--#region main
--#region validate
if not turtle then
    error('Use program in a turtle not computer')
end
local canDig={turtle.dig()}
if canDig == 'No tool to dig with' then
    error('Missing pickaxe')
end
--#endregion validate

Index={}
Amount={}
local image=[[  4              4
518bb5  14bb    5b5
   b      b      b

 1 b     8 8     bb
818b8   814b8    b88
88888   818b8   8888
55555    8 8    5555

9748     88     48
 c79    8118    98
55c5    9749    55]]
term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(1,1)
print('Select generator:  Front   Top   Side')
term.setCursorPos(1,3)
print('Basic generator')
term.setCursorPos(1,7)
print('Double generator')
term.setCursorPos(1,11)
print('Basalt generator')
paintutils.drawImage(paintutils.parseImage(image),19,2)
term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
term.setCursorPos(1,13)

local selection=OptionsRead({'Basic','Double','Basalt'})

ScanInventory()
if selection=='Basic' then
 print('Items needed:')
    print('1 Water Bucket')
    print('1 Lava Bucket')
    print('2 Fuel (Coal, Wood, second Lava Bucket)')
    print('Select direction of inventory (None, Top, Front)')
    local direction=OptionsRead({'None','Top','Front'})
    if BasicGenerator() then
        local file=fs.open('startup/MineGenerator.lua','w')
        file.write(
[[print('')
print('Mining Cobblestone')
while true do
    local space=0 
    for i=1,16 do
       space=space+ turtle.getItemSpace(i)
    end
    if space > 0 then
        turtle.digDown()]])
    if direction=='Top' then
        file.write([[
        turtle.dropUp()]])
    elseif direction=='Front' then
        file.write([[
        turtle.drop()]])
    end
file.write([[
    end
    sleep(1.5)
end]])
file.close()
print('')
print('Empty turtle inventory')
if direction=='Top' then
    print('Place inventory on top of turtle')
elseif direction=='Front' then
    print('Place inventory in front of turtle')
end
print('Restart to start mining')
    end
elseif selection=='Double' then
 print('Items needed:')
    print('1 Water Bucket')
    print('1 Lava Bucket')
    print('14 Building Block (Default: Cobblestone)')
    print('11 Fuel (Coal, Wood, second Lava Bucket)')
    print('Has inventory on top?(Yes, No)')
    local inventory=OptionsRead({'Yes','No'})
    if DoubleFountain() then
        local file=fs.open('startup/MineGenerator.lua','w')
        file.write(
[[print('')
print('Mining Cobblestone')
while true do
    local space=0 
    for i=1,16 do
       space=space+ turtle.getItemSpace(i)
    end
    if space > 1 then 
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.digDown()]])
    if inventory=='Yes' then
        file.write([[
        turtle.dropUp()]])
    end
file.write([[
    end
    sleep(1.4)
end]])
file.close()
print('')
print('Empty turtle inventory')
 if inventory=='Yes' then
    print('Place inventory on top of turtle')
 end
print('Restart to start mining')
    end
elseif selection=='Basalt' then
    print('Items needed:')
    print('2 Soul Soil')
    print('2 Blue Ice')
    print('1 Lava Bucket')
    print('7 Building Block (Default: Cobblestone)')
    print('5 Fuel (Coal, Wood, second Lava Bucket)')
    print('Has inventory on top?(Yes, No)')
    local inventory=OptionsRead({'Yes','No'})
    if BasaltGenerator() then
        local file=fs.open('startup/MineGenerator.lua','w')
        file.write(
[[print('')
print('Mining Basalt')
while true do 
    local space=0 
    for i=1,16 do
       space=space+ turtle.getItemSpace(i)
    end
    if space > 1 then
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.digDown()]])
    if inventory=='Yes' then
        file.write([[
        turtle.dropUp()]])
    end
file.write([[
    end
    sleep(1.4)
end]])
file.close()
print('')
print('Empty turtle inventory')
 if inventory=='Yes' then
    print('Place inventory on top of turtle')
 end
print('Restart to start mining')

    end
end

Speed Controller
content:
local sc = nil
local sm = nil

local function enumerate()
    local pNames = peripheral.getNames()
    for index, pName in ipairs(pNames) do
        local type = peripheral.getType(pName)
        if not sc and type == "Create_RotationSpeedController" then
            sc = peripheral.wrap(pName)
        elseif not sm and type == "Create_Stressometer" then
            sm = peripheral.wrap(pName)
        end
        if sm and sc then
            return true
        end
    end
    return false
end

if not enumerate() then
    error("Failed to locate speed controller and stressometer")
    return
end

local cap = nil
local stress = nil
local nextCalibration = nil
local reverse = sc.getTargetSpeed() < 0

local function recalibrate()
    local measurements = {}

    measurements[0] = {
        speed = sc.getTargetSpeed() ,
        stress = sm.getStress()
    }
    sc.setTargetSpeed(sc.getTargetSpeed()/2)
    sleep(1)
    measurements[1] = {
        speed = sc.getTargetSpeed(),
        stress = sm.getStress()
    }
    local m = (measurements[0]["stress"] - measurements[1]["stress"])/(measurements[0]["speed"]-measurements[1]["speed"])
    local c = measurements[0]["stress"] - m*measurements[0]["speed"]
    -- y = mx + c
    -- x = (y-c)/m
    local x = (sm.getStressCapacity() - c)/m
    local target = 0
    if reverse then
        target = math.max(math.ceil(x), -256)
    else
        target = math.min(math.floor(x),256)
    end
    print("New target speed: " .. target)
    sc.setTargetSpeed(target)
end


while true do
    if sm.getStress() ~= stress or sm.getStressCapacity() ~= cap then
        -- Something has been added to the network that uses or provides stress
        print("Something changed. Due a recalibration")
        nextCalibration = os.clock() + 30
        stress = sm.getStress()
        cap = sm.getStressCapacity()
    end

    if sm.getStress() > sm.getStressCapacity() or nextCalibration and nextCalibration <= os.clock() then
        -- Calibrate the stress of the system
        nextCalibration = nil
        print("Recalibrating...")
        recalibrate()
        sleep(1)
        
        stress = sm.getStress()
        cap = sm.getStressCapacity()
    else
        sleep(1)
    end
end

from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv2D, MaxPooling2D, BatchNormalization, Dropout, Flatten, Dense, SpatialDropout2D
from tensorflow.keras.regularizers import l2
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam

def deeper_custom_cnn(img_size=32, channels=1):
    model = Sequential()
    input_shape = (img_size, img_size, channels)
    
    # First convolutional block
    model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), input_shape=input_shape, activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
    model.add(SpatialDropout2D(0.2))
    
    # Second convolutional block
    model.add(Conv2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Conv2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
    model.add(SpatialDropout2D(0.2))
    
    # Third convolutional block
    model.add(Conv2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Conv2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
    model.add(SpatialDropout2D(0.2))
    
    # Fourth convolutional block (new)
    model.add(Conv2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Conv2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
    model.add(SpatialDropout2D(0.2))
    
    # Fifth convolutional block (new)
    model.add(Conv2D(1024, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Conv2D(1024, (3, 3), activation='relu', padding='same', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)))
    model.add(SpatialDropout2D(0.2))
    
    # Flatten and Dense layers
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.001)))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(21, activation='softmax'))
    
    return model

model = deeper_custom_cnn()
model.summary()

import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow import keras
from keras.models import save_model

# Set the learning rate
optimizer = keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-3)
model.compile(optimizer=optimizer, loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Fit the model
h = model.fit(x=X_train,
              y=y_train,
              batch_size=32,
              epochs=50,
              verbose=1,
              validation_data=(X_val, y_val),
              shuffle=True)

# Save the model
save_model(model, 'custom_cnn_v3_3.h5')

title: Extract the audio track and convert it to MP3
content:
setlocal enabledelayedexpansion

REM Directory with video files
set "DIRECTORY=d:\s4"

REM Iterate over each MKV file in the directory
for %%F in ("%DIRECTORY%\*.mkv") do (
    REM Get the file name without extension
    set "FILE=%%~nF"

    REM Extract the audio track
    ffmpeg -i "%%F" -vn -acodec copy "!DIRECTORY!\!FILE!.ac3"
	
    echo Audio extracted from %%F
)

REM Iterate over each AC3 file in the directory
for %%F in ("%DIRECTORY%\*.ac3") do (
    REM Get the file name without extension
    set "FILE=%%~nF"

    REM Convert to MP3
    ffmpeg -i "%%F" -acodec libmp3lame -q:a 2 "!DIRECTORY!\!FILE!.mp3"
	
    echo File converted to MP3: %%F
)

endlocal
pause

# This opens the file story.txt.
with open("story.txt", "r") as s:
    story = s.read()

# Find words in parentheses
words = set()
beginning_of_word = -1

start_target = "("
end_target = ")"

for i, char in enumerate(story):
    if char == start_target:
        beginning_of_word = i

    if char == end_target and beginning_of_word != -1:
        word = story[beginning_of_word: i + 1]
        words.add(word)
        beginning_of_word = -1

# Get replacements
answers = {}

for word in words:
    answer = input("Enter a word " + word + ": ")
    answers[word] = answer

# Replacing words in the story
for word in words:
    story = story.replace(word, answers[word])

print(story)
